abstract: >
  A conceptual-mathematical research note proposing Perfect Closure as a
  structural principle connecting the Riemann critical line Re(s)=1/2,
  square-rooted prime conjugate phase routes, zeta zeros as completed
  cancellation, quaternionic closure q^6=1, Pauli exclusion as antisymmetric
  cancellation, matter/antimatter as conjugate closure directions, and the
  Faro shuffle return S^8=I.
